docs: update history to include #111 fix

Fixed #111: Segfault on macOS 12.5 / setproctitle 1.3.0

For reasons known only to Apple `_LSApplicationCheckIn` crashes when called from a forked process.
As a workaround I made it to be called only once ever per `exec`-ed image. This means that, as far as Activity Monitor display is concerned, if a parent calls `setproctitle` then forked (but not `exec`-ed) child's call will be ignored. Annoying but there isn't any way around it.

refactor: move python package into pkg subdir

Having it at project level can make imports confusing. If the project
path is added to the path (and it usually is), we may import a non
working version of the package.

This setup breaks `pip install -e`/`python setup.py develop` but tox
works and the former can be worked around (as in psycopg2, where a
complete copy of the package is available in `build`.
